description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for you to join our dynamic, innovative and friendly team dedicated to improving our ward based Clinical Pharmacy services. In this key post you will be working as part of an established multidisciplinary team and be responsible for providing a high quality Clinical Pharmacy service within the Surgical Directorate. As an enthusiastic and supportive patient oriented Pharmacist, you will combine expert opinion and expert practice at the bedside to benefit patient care in a nominated clinical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities of the role include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To co-ordinate the day to day running of the Pharmacy Surgical team and manage junior pharmacists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work closely with the multi-disciplinary team to provide a consistently highly specialist pharmaceutical service to patients within the Surgical Directorate and within other clinical areas as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To support the development of junior pharmacy staff through teaching and supervision including pre-registration pharmacists and diploma students.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To actively participate and lead on improvement initiatives aimed at optimising medicines use and developing clinical services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need post-registration experience relevant to hospital Pharmacy and will have completed a Post Graduate Diploma in General Pharmacy Practice or equivalent qualification. You will need excellent communication, interpersonal and time management skills and will need to enjoy working as part of a team. Your highly developed negotiating skills will enable the resolution of trainee associated problems, whilst motivating pharmacy teams to develop a robust learning culture. You will need notable leadership skills and be able to motivate and inspire staff working with you, promoting the professional role of Pharmacists within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Pharmacy department at London North West University Healthcare NHS Trust is a friendly and forward thinking department that offers comprehensive services including a well-respected Clinical Pharmacy service, a number of Specialist Clinical Pharmacy Pharmacists, and a Regional Medicines Information Centre. The department also has a large manufacturing unit. Northwick Park Hospital is also home to one of eight Hyper Acute Stroke Units (HASUs) in London. The successful candidate will be expected to work Monday – Friday and participate in weekend (Saturday and Sundays) and Bank Holiday rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameShilpa JethwaJob titlePrincipal Pharmacist Clinical Services ManagerEmail addressshilpa.jethwa@nhs.netTelephone number0208 869 2219&lt;/p&gt;
